L3: Orders disappearing / moving to “Not to Ship” when using One Click Upsell (OCU)
https://pluginhive.slack.com/archives/C02E15X8X0C/p1775710954257909
&nbsp;
MCSL customer from Australia using our app for rates and labels, and the website has One Click Upsell (OCU) installed. There are four scenarios observed:
  #1882 – New order without One Click Upsell  User adds product to cart, does not accept any upsell.  User completes checkout and pays.   Order imports into the app correctly.  &nbsp;     #1883 – New order with “in-cart” upsell  User adds product to cart, accepts the discounted “in-cart” upsell, and completes checkout.   Order imports correctly.  &nbsp;     #1884 – New order with “post-purchase” upsell  User adds product to cart, completes checkout, and then accepts a post-purchase upsell with additional payment.  Order imports initially, but when a change is made to the order, the refresh icon appears.   Clicking the refresh moves the order to “Not to Ship” section.  &nbsp;     #1885 – New order with both “in-cart” and “post-purchase” upsells   Similar issue expected as scenario 3.  &nbsp;     Orders with post-purchase upsells are not behaving as expected when refreshed. Customer has shared sample orders for testing.

Please investigate why orders with post-purchase upsells are moved to “Not to Ship” upon refresh.
&nbsp;
